description: Beautiful, comfortable one-bedroom studio apartment in Bayou St John, perfect for 2 or 3. Only 15 minutes from French Quarter/downtown. $200/night, discounts for multiple nights. One block off Bayou St John, the apartment is only 15 minutes from the French Quarter/CBD, perfectly positioned for heading over and back. The place is perfect for a couple, but using a single air mattress (kept here on hand) can add one more in a pinch. The rate does go up a bit for a third person, but not too much. The unit comes fully furnished with couch/futon double bed, bookshelves, AC/heating window unit, and beautiful wall hangings in the front room. description: This is one of the most popular neighborhoods in New Orleans! Bayou St. John is located just two miles from the French Quarter and includes popular bars, restaurants, coffee shops and more. You will truly be blown away by the true New Orleans vibe. This apartment is part of a duplex and is what is called a shotgun layout. All rooms are connected. yes, available by cell or email. Bayou St John offers many local attractions within walking distance.  Restaurants include - Cafe Degas, Sante Fe, Lola's, Toup's Meatery, Parkway Tavern, Luizza's By the Track, 1000 FIGS and Nona Mia. Bars - Pal's Lounge, Bayou Been Garden, Bayou Wine Garden and Swirl. Coffee Shops - CC's Coffee & Fairgrinds. Grocery - Conseco's and Terranova's.  Parks - City Park is located very close and offers many fun attractions including New Orleans Museum of Art and the Sculpture and Botanical Gardens.
